******
Asia
----
- Thailand (Krabi). 6 Aug 2011. Health authorities have highlighted 20
cases of dengue fever on Phi Phi, including some among tourists. There
have been 380 dengue fever cases in Krabi [province], and some
tourists have fallen victim to dengue on Phi Phi and needed treatment
at the island hospital. Cases of dengue have been reduced on Phuket in
the past couple of years. There has been one death on the island in
the 1st 6 months of 2011, the 1st for 2 years.
http://phuketwan.com/tourism/dengue-cases-phi-phi-highlight-community-action-14520/

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of the
Phi Phi islands of Krabi province can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/172A. - Mod.TY]

- Viet Nam. 1 Aug 2011. Since early this year [2011], there have been
approximately 23 000 cases of dengue fever in the country, causing 22
deaths so far. The General Department of Preventive Medicine reported
a total of 5000 cases in July 2011 alone, including 8 fatalities. It
said the number of [dengue virus] infection cases continued rising not
only in the south but also in the north.
http://www.qdnd.vn/qdndsite/en-US/75/72/182/155/188/156128/Default.aspx

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Viet Nam can be accessed
at http://healthmap.org/r/008c. - Mod.TY]

- Philippines (Pampanga). 5 Aug 2011. Governor Lilia Pineda said she
was alarmed by the increasing number of dengue patients admitted at
the Jose B. Lingad (JBL) Memorial Regional Hospital. Pineda said JBL
has recorded not less than 40 confirmed dengue cases, and this is very
alarming considering that the majority of the barangays [neighborhood,
the smallest administrative division in the Philippines] in the
province's 4th district are still submerged in floodwaters.
http://www.sunstar.com.ph/pampanga/local-news/2011/08/05/pampanga-guv-alarmed-dengue-cases-171233

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of the
City of Fernando in Pampanga province can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/15NG. - Mod.TY]

- India (Jharkhand state). 2 Aug 2011. Among 32 blood samples of viral
fever patients sent separately to 3 of the most reputable research
centres in India dealing with specialised diseases, 2 dengue cases
have been detected.
http://telegraphindia.com/1110803/jsp/jharkhand/story_14326702.jsp

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Jharkhand can be accessed
at http://healthmap.org/r/0f1i. - Mod.TY]

- India (Delhi). 2 Aug 2011. According to the MCD statistics on
vector-borne diseases, the number of dengue cases so far this season
has gone up to 15, including 5 new cases reported on Monday [1 Aug
2011]. One dengue death was reported last week from east Delhi.
http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-08-02/delhi/29842018_1_number-of-malaria-cases-mcd-health-dengue-death

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of India showing the location
of Delhi can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/01Jf. - Mod.TY]

- India (Punjab state). 2 Aug 2011. Dengue is spreading fast across
Ludhiana. Seven new cases of dengue have been confirmed in DMC
Hospital Ludhiana. Three cases are from Ludhiana. It was confirmed
after their examination that all of them had contracted dengue.
http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/PUN-LUD-seven-new-cases-of-dengue-in-ludhiana-2317714.html

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of India showing the location
of Ludhiana in Punjab state can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/0Y*N. - Mod.TY]

Caribbean
--------
- Turks and Caicos ex Bahamas and St. Lucia. 7 Aug 2011. Three cases
of dengue fever have been confirmed in the TCI following an outbreak
in neighbouring Bahamas. The 3 adults infected are all imported cases,
2 from the Bahamas and one from St Lucia.
http://healthmap.org/r/172D

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the Turks and Caicos can
be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/172D. - Mod.TY]

- Trinidad and Tobago. 5 Aug 2011. One week after Health Minister Dr
Faud Khan announced there was a dengue outbreak in Trincity, there is
an unconfirmed report that an 8-year-old girl died of the disease
after being discharged from the Eric Williams Medical Sciences
Complex, Mt Hope. The suspected dengue death follows an earlier report
yesterday [4 Aug 2011] that a Claxton Bay woman had to be treated at
hospital for the mosquito-borne disease [virus], triggering fears of
an outbreak in the area.
http://www.newsday.co.tt/news/0,145051.html

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Trinidad and Tobago can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/172E. - Mod.TY]

Latin America
---------------
- Brazil (Rio de Janeiro state). 3 Aug 2011. Dengue has now killed 113
people in Rio de Janeiro state, according to a bulletin issued by the
state Secretariat of Health. The data are for the 30th epidemiological
week that corresponds to 2 Jan-30 Jul 2011. Among the dead, 40 were
registered in the state capital. Suspected [dengue] cases number 154
669, with a peak in April 2011 and a decrease since then.
http://noticias.terra.com.br/brasil/noticias/0,,OI5278572-EI8139,00-RJ+dengue+mata+no+ano+capital+tem+mais+casos.html
[in Portuguese, trans. - Mod.TY].

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Rio de Janeiro state can
be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/00GS. - Mod.TY]
